# MCP Selenium Server Configuration

## MCP Server Setup

The project includes a MCP (Model Context Protocol) server for browser automation using Selenium Grid.

### Configuration

- MCP Server: `src/grid-mcp-server.ts`
- Configuration: `mcp.json`
- Docker Compose: `docker-compose.yml`

### Available Tools

- `open_browser` - Open a new browser instance
- `navigate_to` - Navigate to a URL
- `click_element` - Click on elements
- `type_text` - Type text into fields
- `take_screenshot` - Capture screenshots
- `execute_script` - Run JavaScript
- `get_page_info` - Get page information
- `close_browser` - Close browser session
- `list_sessions` - List active sessions
- `close_all_browsers` - Close all sessions

### Usage

The MCP server manages Docker containers for Selenium Hub and Chrome nodes automatically.
